name: IAM-14
description: v4W.ENko - "IAM-14".  There are five basic patterns are used to draw the abstraction. "Substrate Pattern" is the main trigger for the "MetaBall" algorithm. The central points of "MetaBall" are forming the chrystal with "Delaunay Triangulation". The "Voronoi Diagram" is used to generate the background mesh according to "Substrate Pattern". The most unique here is the central triggers are highlighted with the pattern of the "QuadTree".  The "QaudTree" pattern is forming the dancing squares in front of the abstraction image. Packed as GIF. 1024*1024px / 181 frames.
